<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-16T09:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-16T09:29:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 183.9 Russia/5:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Archangel</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PDC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Poole</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Ambassador in
                                France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-16T18:00:00+03:31">December 16, 1918—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 17—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>37. For <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel House</persName>.
                                <persName>Maklikoff</persName><note n="3" xml:id="d299fn3">
                                <persName>V. A. Maklikoff</persName>, appointed by the Russian
                                Provisional Government as Ambassador to France.</note> has
                            telegraphed <persName>Tchikowski</persName><note n="4" xml:id="d299fn4">
                                <persName>N. V. Tchikowski</persName>, President of the Russian
                                Government of the Northern Region.</note> from Paris saying that
                            while the absence of a proper Russian Government excludes Russia from
                            official representation at the Peace Conference it is hoped to have
                            certain unofficial representatives and it would be well in
                                <persName>Maklikoff</persName>’s view if
                                <persName>Tchikowski</persName> were among these. The latter has
                            replied that he will come if he can arrange to commit his duties at
                            Archangel to other hands. He hopes that General Meuller who is now on
                            the way here from Rome can replace him. He could then reach Paris before
                            the end of January.</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName>Noulens</persName><note n="5" xml:id="d299fn5">
                                <persName>Joseph Noulens</persName>, French Ambassador to
                                Russia.</note> left here yesterday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Poole</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>